$a = random(18,40,2);
$k = random(220,300,1);

BEGIN_TEXT
Question 8:
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
The height in centimeters of the tip of the minute hand on a vertical clock is a function, $BITALIC f(t)${EITALIC}, of the time, $BITALIC t${EITALIC}, in minutes.  The minute hand is $a cm long, and the middle of the clock face is $k cm above the ground.
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
a) The midline of the graph of $BITALIC f(t) $EITALIC is \( y = \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} (include \{ htmlLink("javascript:unitspopup()","units") \} in your answer)
$BR
b) The amplitude of the graph of $BITALIC f(t) $EITALIC is \{ ans_rule(10) \} (include \{ htmlLink("javascript:unitspopup()","units") \} in your answer)
END_TEXT

ANS( num_cmp( $k, units=>'cm' ) );
ANS( num_cmp( $a, units=>'cm' ) );

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR 
a) Since the middle of the clock's face is at $k cm, the midline is \( y = $k \ \mbox{cm} \).
$BR $SPACE $BR
b) Since the hand is $a cm long, the amplitude is \( $a \ \mbox{cm} \).
$BR
END_SOLUTION
      

